**[1863, 04-21] Ms.A.7.3, pp. 120-21**

Caroline Weston to Mary Estlin

Expressions of love and “communion,” even when their correspondence is
temporarily interrupted. Consoles about death of John B. Estlin.
“Formerly we were a {u}Pro-Slavery Nation{/u} … {u}Now{/u} God be
thanked we are an {u}Anti-Slavery Nation{/u}.”


